sequenceDiagram
    actor U as You
    participant T as Trezor Safe 3
    participant A as Treza agent
    participant S as ssh / git
    participant R as Server

    Note over U,T: 1. Unlock the device
    U->>T: Enter PIN (scrambled, on device)
    T->>T: Decrypt the seed in secure storage
    opt Passphrase enabled
        U->>T: Enter passphrase
        T->>T: Derive hidden-wallet seed
    end

    Note over U,R: 2. One-time — publish the public key
    U->>A: Add identity ssh://user@host, click Export
    A->>T: GetPublicKey(path = SLIP-0013 hash of identity)
    T->>T: Derive key pair for that path
    T-->>U: "Export SSH public key?"
    U->>T: Confirm
    T-->>A: Public key only (private key stays on device)
    A-->>U: authorized_keys line
    U->>R: Add line to ~/.ssh/authorized_keys (or GitHub)

    Note over U,R: 3. Every login — challenge / response
    S->>R: Connect, offer the public key
    R-->>S: Random challenge (prove you hold the private key)
    S->>A: Sign request over named pipe / SSH_AUTH_SOCK
    A->>T: SignIdentity(challenge)
    T-->>U: "Sign SSH login for user@host?"
    U->>T: Confirm
    T->>T: Sign challenge with the private key (never leaves)
    T-->>A: Signature
    A-->>S: Signature
    S->>R: Signature
    R->>R: Verify against the stored public key
    R-->>U: Access granted
